pageContext.claim: “If the Wall Street Journal 'Editorial' writers had called, as they should have, they would have easily found that I was “'NOT happy with the Georgia Governor on Tuesday night.' You said the opposite, and got it wrong as you often do!”
pageContext.analysis: Trump first gave Kemp permission to open up faster than the federal guidelines before abruptly changing in his mind. In a phone call with the nation’s governors, as Kemp was making plans to lift coronavirus restrictions, Trump told the governor he was doing a “great job,” according to audio obtained by The Washington Post. Kemp thanked Trump for working with his state and said he had spoken to the president and Vice President Pence about reopening Georgia’s economy and was trying to emulate Trump’s approach. “Our folks are really looking forward to that. I'm sure the whole country is,” Kemp said on the call. “We're going to dig in and get ready to go.”
